// .claude/settings.local.json.example
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// TEMPLATE ONLY. Claude Code does NOT load this file — it loads
// .claude/settings.local.json (no ".example"). Copy ONE of the tiers below into
// that file to opt in. .claude/settings.local.json is gitignored and stays local.
//
// (JSON has no comments; strip the // lines when you copy a block.)
//
// What this enables: the committed PreToolUse hook at
// .claude/hooks/web-approve.py auto-approves web calls so a search run doesn't
// stop at a prompt on every page. It is allowlist-based on purpose — see below.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

// ===========================================================================
// TIER (a) — RECOMMENDED. Allowlist-gated WebFetch + read-only WebSearch.
// ===========================================================================
// WebSearch is auto-approved (it only returns snippets — there is no channel for
// it to send your data anywhere). WebFetch is auto-approved ONLY for hosts on your
// local .claude/web-allowlist.txt (exact host or a dot-boundary subdomain); every
// other fetch still prompts. This keeps the convenience for the sites you actually
// search while a fetch to a novel/untrusted domain — the realistic exfiltration
// risk — still stops for your confirmation.
//
// Setup:
//   1. Copy the JSON object below into .claude/settings.local.json
//   2. Create .claude/web-allowlist.txt with one host per line, e.g.:
//        charityjob.co.uk
//        greenhouse.io
//      (subdomains like boards.greenhouse.io match automatically)
//
// {
//   "permissions": {
//     "allow": ["WebSearch"]
//   },
//   "hooks": {
//     "PreToolUse": [
//       {
//         "matcher": "WebFetch|WebSearch",
//         "hooks": [
//           {
//             "type": "command",
//             "command": "python3 \"${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/.claude/hooks/web-approve.py\""
//           }
//         ]
//       }
//     ]
//   }
// }

// ===========================================================================
// TIER (b) — ALTERNATIVE (weaker; understand the tradeoff before using).
// ===========================================================================
// Blanket auto-approve of every WebFetch and WebSearch — no allowlist, nothing
// prompts. More convenient, but it removes the one stop that would catch a fetch
// to an attacker-chosen domain. RISK: if your profile holds sensitive data, a
// prompt-injection or a mistaken URL could exfiltrate it with no confirmation.
// Tier (a) is the default for exactly this reason. Only use (b) on a profile you
// are comfortable fetching anywhere from.
//
// {
//   "permissions": {
//     "allow": ["WebFetch", "WebSearch"]
//   }
// }
